# Planned cross docking

# Released in version 10.0.5
#
# About

This functionality introduces advanced planned cross docking where the inventory quantity required to satisfy an order will be directed to the correct outbound dock or staging area straight from receipt or creation. All remaining inventory from the inbound source will be directed to the correct storage location through regular put away process. This warehouse process is called cross docking.

Cross docking therefore allows the worker to skip inbound put away and outbound picking of inventory that is already marked to an outbound order. The result is minimized number of touches of inventory where possible, together with greater time and space savings on the warehouse shop floor due to less interaction with the system.

Prior to execution, the user must configure new cross dock template where the supply source as well as other sets of requirements for cross docking are specified. As the outbound order is created, the line must be marked against an inbound order containing identical item.

At the time of inbound order receiving, cross docking setup will automatically identify the need for a cross dock and create the movement work for required quantity based on location directive setup.

# Setup

## Cross Dock Template

Navigate to _Warehouse management_ _-_ _Setup - Work - Cross docking templates._ Create a new template and specify the following:

- Sequence – order in which the templates will evaluated – 1
- Cross docking template ID – 51
- Description – Warehouse 51
- Demand release policy – Before supply receipt
- Warehouse – 51

### Planning

The planning section controls how the template will work.

Demand requirements:

- Demand requirements – What is required for cross docking to be created – None

Work creation:

- Location type – Should the cross dock work use the staging/load locations from the shipment, or use location directives to find its own – Shipment locations
- Work template – Optionally specify a work template that should be used – Blank
- Revalidate on supply receipt – Controls if the maximum window and expiration days should be rechecked when receiving the supply - No
- Validate time window – Should the system validate that the receipt and ship dates are within the specified maximum window? – No
- Maximum time window – 5
- Maximum time window unit – Days
- Minimum time window – 0
- Minimum time window unit – Days

FEFO Criteria

- Expiration days range – 0

### Supply source

In the supply source you specify what types of supply are valid for this template.

Add Purchase order as Sequence number 1.

## Work Class

Navigate to _Warehouse management_ __ _Setup_ __ _Work_ __ _Work classes_ and create a new work class

- Work class ID – CrossDock
- Description – Cross Dock
- Work order type – Cross docking

## Work template

Navigate to _Warehouse management_ __ _Setup_ __ _Work_ __ _Work templates_ and change the Work order type to &#39;Cross docking&#39;.

Create a new work template:

- Sequence number – 1
- Work template – 51 Cross Dock
- Work template description – 51 Cross Dock

Create a line:

- Work type – Pick
- Work class ID – CrossDock

Create a second line:

- Work type – Put
- Work class ID – CrossDock

Save the work template and ensure it becomes valid.

## Location directives

Navigate to _Warehouse management - Setup - Location directives_ and change the Work order type to &#39;Cross docking&#39;

Create a new location directive:

- Sequence number – 1
- Name: 51 Cross Dock Put
- Work type: Put
- Site: 5
- Warehouse: 51

Create a line:

- From quantity: 1
- To quantity: 1,000,000

Create an action:

- Name: Baydoor

In the query specify Location = BAYDOOR

## Mobile device menu item

Navigate to _Warehouse management - Setup - Mobile device - Mobile device menu items._ Select &#39;Purchase Put-away&#39;

In the Work classes FastTab, add a new line for Work class ID: CrossDock.

# Process

## Purchase order

Navigate to _Procurement and sourcing - Purchase orders - All purchase orders_ and create a new purchase order.

Set the Vendor account = 104 and Warehouse = 51.

Add a line to the PO for item A0001, quantity 5 pcs.

## Sales order

Navigate to _Sales and marketing - Sales orders - All sales order_ and create a new sales order.

Set the Customer account = US-002 and the Warehouse = 51.

Add a line for item A0001, quantity 3 pcs.

## Create Planned Cross Dock

From the Warehouse _-_ Actions section of the ribbon, click on Release to warehouse. This will create a shipment and load line for the sales order line, and attempt to allocate inventory. Because there is no inventory in the warehouse, you will see a warning &quot;No work was created.&quot; This is expected.

Click on Warehouse _-_ Shipment details in the order lines action bar.

In the load lines section of the shipment details, notice that the &#39;Planned cross docking quantity&#39; field is set to 3. Because there was no inventory available in the warehouse, but there is a valid supply source arriving within the window defined on the cross docking template.

You can click on &#39;Planned cross docking&#39; in the load lines action bar to see details of the cross docking that was created.

## Process Cross Dock

Open the mobile device, log in to warehouse 51, and navigate to _Inbound - Purchase Receive_.

Enter your purchase order number and item that you create earlier, and that the planned cross dock is created against. Enter the full quantity of the line. Click OK.

The system will receive the 5 from the purchase order, and create two pieces of work.

The first work ID, with Work order type = Cross docking is linked to the sales order, has a quantity of 3, and is directed to the final shipping location to be immediately shipped out.

The second work ID, with Work order type = Purchase orders, is linked to the purchase order, and has the remainder of the quantity that was not cross docked associated with it to put away to storage.

Both work ID&#39;s currently have the same target LP. On the mobile device, navigate to _Inbound - Purchase Put-away_ and enter the target LP from the work.

The system will prompt you to pick the cross dock work first, and then ask for a new target LP for the quantity being cross docked. The original target LP generated during receiving will remain with the quantity being putaway.
